I love this song!
Girls, let's dance!

00:27:43.431 --> 00:27:45.225
Come on! Hurry, let’s dance!

00:27:45.225 --> 00:27:46.184
Okay, fine!

00:27:46.184 --> 00:27:47.686
Come on, come on.
We’ll get to that later.

00:27:51.564 --> 00:27:52.524
Happy Birthday!

00:27:52.524 --> 00:27:53.525
Thank you.

00:28:04.911 --> 00:28:05.995
Ke! Don’t leave me!

00:28:05.995 --> 00:28:06.621
Wait!

00:28:06.621 --> 00:28:08.123
- Hey.
- Sorry, Sam. I’m leaving.

00:28:08.123 --> 00:28:08.998
- Huh? Why?
- Wait!

00:28:08.998 --> 00:28:09.916
- Hey—
- Sorry.

00:28:09.916 --> 00:28:11.793
Ke! Don’t leave me! Ke!

00:28:11.793 --> 00:28:13.545
What? What’s happening?

00:28:16.339 --> 00:28:17.132
Via?

00:28:17.132 --> 00:28:18.216
Larkin, what are you doing?

00:28:19.134 --> 00:28:20.135
What the—

00:28:20.802 --> 00:28:21.820
Hey—

00:28:22.387 --> 00:28:23.388
Wow.

00:28:23.805 --> 00:28:25.552
I’m so confused right now.

00:28:25.577 --> 00:28:27.454
Kino, let go of me!

00:28:28.024 --> 00:28:29.025
What the hell?

00:28:31.532 --> 00:28:33.205
Sir, I’ll tell you when
we’re about to leave, okay?

00:28:34.149 --> 00:28:35.150
What the hell?

00:28:37.542 --> 00:28:38.710
Via, I’m sorry.

00:28:39.028 --> 00:28:39.988
I’m really sorry.

00:28:40.319 --> 00:28:41.923
Shit. I’m sorry, please.

00:28:42.081 --> 00:28:44.292
What are you even
apologizing about?

00:28:45.660 --> 00:28:47.036
All I ever hear
from you is “sorry"

00:28:47.036 --> 00:28:48.913
whenever we talk, Kino.

00:28:49.257 --> 00:28:51.050
Don’t you have
anything else to say?

00:28:52.959 --> 00:28:54.753
Via, I just wanted to
talk to you because

00:28:54.753 --> 00:28:58.256
I’ve been texting you, calling you,
and you’re not answering.

00:28:58.256 --> 00:29:00.675
I gave you space to calm down.

00:29:01.316 --> 00:29:03.818
But Via, it’s been weeks.

00:29:04.068 --> 00:29:06.946
So please, talk to me, Via.

00:29:07.974 --> 00:29:09.768
What? What do you want?

00:29:09.768 --> 00:29:11.936
Do you want me to enroll? Again?

00:29:11.936 --> 00:29:13.646
Fine, I’ll enroll next semester.

00:29:13.897 --> 00:29:15.190
Is it the acting thing?

00:29:15.190 --> 00:29:16.649
You don’t want me
doing that anymore?

00:29:16.649 --> 00:29:18.109
Fine, I won’t take
any more projects.

00:29:18.271 --> 00:29:19.481
I’ll just finish the—

00:29:19.506 --> 00:29:21.633
What are you even talking about?

00:29:27.744 --> 00:29:28.745
Via…

00:29:31.787 --> 00:29:33.372
Via, I don’t even know anymore.

00:29:37.962 --> 00:29:39.088
Via, I’m sorry.

00:29:39.439 --> 00:29:41.858
I’m sorry, I’m just scared, okay?

00:29:41.883 --> 00:29:43.885
I’m scared that
if I do something

00:29:43.885 --> 00:29:46.304
you don’t like, you’ll leave me.

00:29:47.187 --> 00:29:48.741
This isn’t an excuse, Via.

00:29:48.766 --> 00:29:49.808
I know I messed up.

00:29:49.808 --> 00:29:51.893
I should’ve told you
even if you didn’t like it,

00:29:51.893 --> 00:29:53.895
even if you didn’t
want to hear it.

00:29:57.232 --> 00:29:58.316
But Via…

00:29:59.150 --> 00:30:00.401
What about me?

00:30:02.278 --> 00:30:03.648
This is what I want.

00:30:14.874 --> 00:30:17.252
Why do I always
stop you from thriving?

00:30:17.806 --> 00:30:20.563
I’m joining the photojournalism
club next school year.

00:30:20.681 --> 00:30:23.476
Aside from music,
I like cameras too.

00:30:26.344 --> 00:30:29.138
Why do I always project
my scars onto you?

00:30:29.806 --> 00:30:31.140
Kino, you’re lucky,
you know that?

00:30:31.140 --> 00:30:34.405
You already know what you
want to do in life,

00:30:34.430 --> 00:30:36.039
and you’re good at everything.

00:30:36.734 --> 00:30:38.360
If you weren’t around,

00:30:38.385 --> 00:30:40.011
I probably wouldn’t
know what to do either.

00:30:40.036 --> 00:30:41.580
Of course you would.

00:30:41.605 --> 00:30:43.273
When you become an actor,

00:30:43.298 --> 00:30:44.633
I might actually be
your number one fan.

00:30:46.385 --> 00:30:49.008
Why do I keep forcing
what I want on you?

00:31:03.656 --> 00:31:04.719
I’m sorry.

00:31:08.520 --> 00:31:11.617
I just wanted you
to finish school.

00:31:14.392 --> 00:31:17.270
I thought that’s what you wanted.

00:31:21.190 --> 00:31:22.191
But—

00:31:24.652 --> 00:31:26.988
I didn’t realize
I was stopping you

00:31:26.988 --> 00:31:29.407
from doing the things
you want to do.

00:31:36.944 --> 00:31:38.905
Kino, I’m sorry.

00:31:40.627 --> 00:31:42.754
I’m sorry.

00:31:44.088 --> 00:31:46.674
I’m sorry you’re struggling.

00:31:46.674 --> 00:31:50.484
I’m sorry that the way
I love hurts. I’m sorry.

00:32:04.025 --> 00:32:05.735
Via, I know what
I did was wrong.

00:32:05.735 --> 00:32:08.029
I should’ve told you
from the very beginning.

00:32:08.613 --> 00:32:11.783
I know I’ve hurt you a lot.

00:32:12.825 --> 00:32:14.452
But I’m telling you right now,

00:32:14.452 --> 00:32:16.371
I won’t make
promises anymore, okay?

00:32:17.121 --> 00:32:18.623
I’ll just tell you everything.

00:32:18.623 --> 00:32:21.542
Whatever you want to know,
whatever’s happening to me.

00:32:21.542 --> 00:32:24.253
I’ll tell you everything.
Just please, don’t leave me.

00:32:33.972 --> 00:32:37.225
I won’t rely
on your words anymore.

00:32:40.603 --> 00:32:42.547
But I’ll believe you.

00:32:48.778 --> 00:32:51.155
Do you really like
what you’re doing?

00:32:59.956 --> 00:33:02.125
I’m not leaving your side.

00:33:05.545 --> 00:33:07.755
I’ll trust you,

00:33:08.719 --> 00:33:11.469
but Kino, you have
to trust me too, okay?

00:33:17.265 --> 00:33:20.435
Promise me too
that you’ll never think

00:33:20.435 --> 00:33:22.766
that you’re a burden
to what I’m doing.

00:33:23.396 --> 00:33:25.305
Because you’re not, Via. Okay?

00:33:50.764 --> 00:33:54.267
After all that,
Arkin and I were okay again.

00:33:54.549 --> 00:33:58.845
Just like he promised,
he told me everything.

00:33:59.328 --> 00:34:01.859
And slowly,
my trust in him came back.

00:34:02.812 --> 00:34:06.441
The only problem was,
he told me literally everything.

00:34:09.025 --> 00:34:10.610
Months passed,

00:34:11.063 --> 00:34:13.446
and Kino’s projects kept
coming one after another.

00:34:13.695 --> 00:34:16.883
So did the big
milestones in his life.

00:34:17.071 --> 00:34:19.157
Like his new car.

00:34:24.540 --> 00:34:25.666
What’s up, Via?

00:34:25.666 --> 00:34:27.919
Check out my new condo.

00:34:27.919 --> 00:34:30.713
It’s so nice here. It’s huge!

00:34:31.406 --> 00:34:34.201
And look at this,

00:34:34.226 --> 00:34:37.426
the sofa’s super relaxing.

00:34:37.451 --> 00:34:38.648
There’s a bit of
an overlooking view, too.

00:34:39.106 --> 00:34:41.400
Even when he moved
into his new condo unit,

00:34:42.058 --> 00:34:46.734
he always made sure that
even if we rarely saw each other,

00:34:46.759 --> 00:34:48.883
I was still part of his success.

00:34:51.070 --> 00:34:53.781
I’m happy for everything
he’s achieving.

00:34:55.800 --> 00:35:00.221
But am I happy with
my own achievements?

00:35:10.986 --> 00:35:12.237
You can do this.

00:35:12.877 --> 00:35:14.128
You really can.

00:35:15.258 --> 00:35:16.717
You can do this.

00:35:25.246 --> 00:35:26.539
You got this.

00:35:46.914 --> 00:35:48.124
Via, you’re okay.

00:35:48.124 --> 00:35:50.168
Don’t let this get to you.
You’re fine.

00:35:50.168 --> 00:35:51.627
You can do this.

00:36:10.450 --> 00:36:13.124
I’m getting excited
about our project.

00:36:13.149 --> 00:36:18.863
We’re supposed to
draw our dream project.

00:36:19.113 --> 00:36:22.158
I already have so many ideas!

00:36:22.158 --> 00:36:25.494
Me? I want my own
architecture firm.

00:36:25.786 --> 00:36:26.537
Wow!

00:36:26.537 --> 00:36:28.706
Floor-to-ceiling windows, modern.

00:36:28.706 --> 00:36:29.707
Yes.

00:36:29.707 --> 00:36:31.626
And a garden on the rooftop.

00:36:31.626 --> 00:36:34.003
Actually, that sounds so nice!

00:36:34.003 --> 00:36:40.968
As for me, I want to do
my dream house, ranch-style.

00:36:40.968 --> 00:36:45.640
So it feels cozy, warm, and—

00:36:45.640 --> 00:36:48.726
an open floor layout,
so while I’m cooking

00:36:48.726 --> 00:36:51.312
I can see my
husband and my kids.

00:36:51.312 --> 00:36:53.231
Like, hi! Just like that!

00:36:53.231 --> 00:36:54.190
Right?

00:36:55.816 --> 00:36:57.235
What about you, Via?

00:37:04.200 --> 00:37:05.952
That’s how many now?

00:37:07.370 --> 00:37:08.287
I don’t know.

00:37:08.287 --> 00:37:09.997
I don’t even know
what to do anymore.

00:37:09.997 --> 00:37:14.252
I don’t even know
what I really want.

00:37:14.252 --> 00:37:16.170
I don’t even have
a dream project yet.

00:37:16.462 --> 00:37:18.965
Don’t worry. It will come.

00:37:18.990 --> 00:37:20.023
Right.

00:37:20.048 --> 00:37:21.800
Here, this might help
you get motivated.

00:37:21.926 --> 00:37:23.052
Just think that one day,

00:37:23.052 --> 00:37:25.179
we’ll be designing the buildings
here in the Philippines.

00:37:25.846 --> 00:37:27.701
And people are gonna say,

00:37:27.726 --> 00:37:31.686
“that was designed by
Architect Valeria, Architect Ynares,

00:37:31.686 --> 00:37:33.020
and Architect—

00:37:33.222 --> 00:37:34.807
- Diaz.”
- Diaz.

00:37:35.356 --> 00:37:36.983
So exciting, right?

00:37:36.983 --> 00:37:38.567
Aren’t you excited, Via?

00:37:38.567 --> 00:37:39.648
Aren’t you?

00:37:41.946 --> 00:37:43.364
I don’t know. I feel like—

00:37:43.854 --> 00:37:46.731
I feel like I kind of regret
taking this course.

00:37:48.047 --> 00:37:49.304
You know what I mean?

00:37:49.537 --> 00:37:51.580
It’s like I’m only finishing it
because I have to.

00:37:51.580 --> 00:37:53.165
I’m just forcing
myself at this point.

00:37:53.165 --> 00:37:54.834
I don’t want to
waste the tuition.

00:37:55.166 --> 00:37:57.968
I don’t want to waste Papa
and my aunt’s savings too.

00:38:02.174 --> 00:38:04.635
Via, come on. I understand you.

00:38:04.635 --> 00:38:07.179
Our program is really hard.
Even I’m struggling.

00:38:07.179 --> 00:38:09.181
But I know you can do it.

00:38:09.181 --> 00:38:12.560
Your ideas and your
plates are really good.

00:38:14.770 --> 00:38:17.398
Your work is so neat.
So polished.

00:38:17.398 --> 00:38:20.276
Honestly, you’re even
better than me

00:38:20.276 --> 00:38:21.527
at being an architect.

00:38:21.736 --> 00:38:24.280
And that’s why we told you
we’d support you.

00:38:24.780 --> 00:38:25.906
You can do it.

00:38:25.906 --> 00:38:28.784
The three of us can do it
as long as we stick together.

00:38:28.784 --> 00:38:31.287
Until we graduate.

00:38:31.707 --> 00:38:37.691
Until we get our licenses and
become successful architects.

00:38:38.044 --> 00:38:39.045
Right?

00:38:39.879 --> 00:38:41.672
Thank you, really.

00:38:42.631 --> 00:38:43.924
You guys help me so much.

00:38:43.924 --> 00:38:47.762
I can’t imagine doing
this without you.

00:38:49.221 --> 00:38:50.014
Let’s hug.

00:38:50.014 --> 00:38:51.265
Oh my gosh.

00:38:52.975 --> 00:38:54.101
We got this.

00:38:54.101 --> 00:38:55.728
The three of us
can definitely do this.

00:38:55.728 --> 00:38:57.897
Yes! Fight!

00:38:59.106 --> 00:39:00.223
Fight.

00:39:00.858 --> 00:39:03.569
Hey guys, they said Clea’s
getting a new partner.

00:39:03.569 --> 00:39:07.448
Some new actor who already
has a bunch of projects.

00:39:07.448 --> 00:39:08.699
Who?

00:39:09.658 --> 00:39:10.659
Larkin?

00:39:10.659 --> 00:39:11.619
Larkin Sanchez.

00:39:11.619 --> 00:39:13.184
I think they’re trying
to boost his popularity.

00:39:13.454 --> 00:39:16.040
I read about that too.
It’s not official yet.

00:39:16.248 --> 00:39:20.795
Yeah, but look at
everyone’s reactions online.

00:39:21.045 --> 00:39:22.671
The edits of them together
already have so many views.

00:39:22.671 --> 00:39:25.883
And their pairing in that series
is starting to blow up, too.

00:39:26.217 --> 00:39:30.429
Their chemistry is crazy,
even in their tiny scenes. Look.

00:39:30.429 --> 00:39:31.972
I mean, I’m a fan of Clea too,

00:39:31.972 --> 00:39:33.949
but I hope she doesn’t
get a love team.

00:39:33.974 --> 00:39:35.726
She’s fine on her own.

00:39:36.102 --> 00:39:38.354
Why don’t you want
her in a love team?

00:39:38.354 --> 00:39:39.647
I just don’t.

00:39:40.074 --> 00:39:42.316
There’s a high chance
she might catch feelings

00:39:42.316 --> 00:39:43.684
for her love team partner.

00:39:44.193 --> 00:39:47.488
Enough with these love teams
turning into real-life couples.

00:39:47.488 --> 00:39:50.074
Wow, you’re such
a possessive fan.

00:39:50.074 --> 00:39:52.618
Fine, okay. No more. I’ll stop.

00:39:52.618 --> 00:39:54.078
There, look. Deleted.

00:39:54.078 --> 00:39:55.287
No more.

00:39:56.784 --> 00:39:59.121
Why am I even feeling like this?

00:39:59.583 --> 00:40:01.988
I don’t have the
right to be jealous.

00:40:03.129 --> 00:40:04.964
We’re just friends.

00:40:17.935 --> 00:40:20.479
This concert hall
is my dream project.

00:40:20.646 --> 00:40:23.023
My classmates all chose
houses or office buildings

00:40:23.023 --> 00:40:24.567
for their dream projects.

00:40:24.567 --> 00:40:26.444
But this is mine.

00:40:27.361 --> 00:40:28.362
It’s okay, right?

00:40:28.863 --> 00:40:29.864
Does it look good?

00:40:39.081 --> 00:40:40.082
Are you okay?

00:40:49.258 --> 00:40:50.843
They’re pairing me with someone.

00:40:52.261 --> 00:40:53.262
Pairing?

00:40:55.181 --> 00:40:58.684
Remember I told you that
after my series project,

00:40:59.185 --> 00:41:00.436
I’d be doing a movie?

00:41:01.645 --> 00:41:03.230
That movie is
finally pushing through.

00:41:04.732 --> 00:41:05.782
Really?

00:41:06.150 --> 00:41:07.401
Then congrats!

00:41:09.612 --> 00:41:11.822
Why do you look like
you’re not happy, though?

00:41:15.868 --> 00:41:19.121
Management wants to try
pairing me with a love interest.

00:41:19.830 --> 00:41:22.208
And if people like it,

00:41:23.334 --> 00:41:25.044
they might make us
an official love team.

00:41:25.241 --> 00:41:26.367
I don’t want that.

00:41:31.425 --> 00:41:33.260
But that’s good for your career.

00:41:34.512 --> 00:41:35.971
Who are they pairing you with?

00:41:37.097 --> 00:41:38.098
Clea.

00:41:40.726 --> 00:41:42.019
Clea Aguilar?

00:41:42.811 --> 00:41:44.396
You don’t know
Clea Zorel Aguilar?

00:41:44.647 --> 00:41:46.690
That’s the former child star.

00:41:46.690 --> 00:41:48.567
We’re basically the same age.

00:41:48.567 --> 00:41:50.069
But she’s super famous now.

00:41:51.654 --> 00:41:52.747
Yeah.

00:41:53.989 --> 00:41:56.492
She’s one of the most popular
actresses right now, right?

00:41:57.326 --> 00:41:58.744
That’s really good for you.

00:41:58.744 --> 00:42:00.538
It’ll help your career a lot.

00:42:01.956 --> 00:42:03.916
And it’s just a love team.

00:42:03.916 --> 00:42:06.585
You don’t actually have
to date her in real life.

00:42:09.451 --> 00:42:10.619
That’s true.

00:42:11.465 --> 00:42:13.801
And it’s not like
I have a choice anyway.

00:42:13.801 --> 00:42:15.928
I just follow whatever
my manager tells me.

00:42:16.887 --> 00:42:19.265
It’s a big deal for your career.

00:42:19.452 --> 00:42:21.120
And if you think about it,

00:42:21.559 --> 00:42:25.396
all of this is to help you
reach your dreams.

00:42:27.988 --> 00:42:29.450
Are you really okay with it?

00:42:33.904 --> 00:42:35.114
Of course.

00:42:35.447 --> 00:42:38.075
Didn’t I tell you I’ll support
you in everything?

00:42:38.521 --> 00:42:41.399
I’m excited to see you
reach your dreams.

00:42:43.330 --> 00:42:45.249
Via, I’m saying
sorry in advance, okay?

00:42:45.249 --> 00:42:49.920
I might get really busy
in the next few weeks.

00:42:49.920 --> 00:42:52.631
Once we start rolling,
it’s nonstop.

00:42:53.603 --> 00:42:56.536
He’ll be with Clea
the whole day on set.

00:42:58.804 --> 00:43:00.055
Well…

00:43:01.015 --> 00:43:05.311
Then let’s just meet
on your day off.

00:43:06.729 --> 00:43:08.272
Sure, let’s do that.

00:43:08.689 --> 00:43:10.774
Sometimes my manager
makes me go to the gym too.

00:43:10.774 --> 00:43:13.193
But Sevi goes with me,
so don’t worry.

00:43:16.614 --> 00:43:18.616
Don’t worry about me, Kino.

00:43:20.409 --> 00:43:22.411
I’m just here to support you.

00:43:22.703 --> 00:43:23.954
Thank you, Via.

00:43:48.312 --> 00:43:49.730
They don’t even look
good together.

00:43:49.878 --> 00:43:51.171
What did you say?

00:43:52.544 --> 00:43:53.606
Nothing!

00:43:53.631 --> 00:43:55.090
I didn’t say anything.

00:43:55.957 --> 00:43:57.046
By the way, where’s Arkin?

00:43:57.071 --> 00:43:58.572
He hasn’t been showing up.

00:43:59.615 --> 00:44:00.699
He’s busy.

00:44:00.699 --> 00:44:03.535
If it’s not work,
he’s at the gym with Sevi.

00:44:03.535 --> 00:44:05.913
Wow, Sevi’s stealing your title.

00:44:05.913 --> 00:44:07.706
He’s the new best friend.

00:44:09.249 --> 00:44:10.551
Hey.

00:44:11.219 --> 00:44:12.426
Now you—

00:44:16.090 --> 00:44:19.145
Finally, I’m free.
Let’s go to Sunken?

00:44:19.674 --> 00:44:20.800
Shooting starts
again tomorrow.

00:44:21.512 --> 00:44:23.389
I’m on my way.

00:44:23.935 --> 00:44:26.313
Luna, Ke, I’ll go ahead, okay?

00:44:26.338 --> 00:44:29.328
Kino texted me. He’s free,
so we’re meeting later.

00:44:29.353 --> 00:44:30.312
Okay.

00:44:30.312 --> 00:44:32.481
And can you put my t-square
in the locker, please?

00:44:32.481 --> 00:44:35.109
- Bye!
- All right, take care. Hey!

00:44:38.362 --> 00:44:39.363
- Via!
- Kino.

00:44:41.281 --> 00:44:42.825
How are you? You okay?

00:44:51.834 --> 00:44:54.628
Wow, you’re wearing lip tint.

00:44:56.463 --> 00:44:58.465
Is only Clea allowed to wear lip tint?

00:44:59.216 --> 00:45:00.509
You’re so annoying.

00:45:02.902 --> 00:45:04.195
Why am I annoying?

00:45:14.541 --> 00:45:16.309
Your hair’s a mess again.

00:45:16.734 --> 00:45:18.485
Come here, I’ll tie it.

00:45:25.701 --> 00:45:26.994
Can you do it?

00:45:41.300 --> 00:45:42.301
There.

00:45:44.833 --> 00:45:46.001
Thanks.

00:45:47.014 --> 00:45:49.808
So, why’d you ask me
to meet you today?

00:45:52.227 --> 00:45:53.937
Via, I’m releasing a single.

00:45:54.396 --> 00:45:56.607
Remember the song
I was writing before?

00:45:57.649 --> 00:45:58.650
I finished it.

00:45:59.404 --> 00:46:00.405
I want you to hear it.

00:46:01.921 --> 00:46:03.214
Listen carefully, okay?

00:46:10.177 --> 00:46:15.265
♪ Left thinking in the
midst of the chaos, ♪

00:46:16.960 --> 00:46:22.508
♪ utterly bewildered
by these feelings. ♪

00:46:22.533 --> 00:46:27.996
♪ I can't tell if this is a dream, ♪

00:46:28.430 --> 00:46:34.853
♪ as if my heart was
playing in the heavens. ♪

00:46:35.361 --> 00:46:40.825
♪ In the daylight
you are there, ♪

00:46:41.318 --> 00:46:46.990
♪ beside me, and I gaze at you. ♪

00:46:47.533 --> 00:46:49.910
♪ I don't know anymore, ♪

00:46:50.536 --> 00:46:59.086
♪ I get confused whenever
I'm with you in… ♪

00:47:00.003 --> 00:47:08.262
♪ A golden scenery
beneath the sky, ♪

00:47:08.262 --> 00:47:13.308
♪ having you with me. ♪

00:47:13.308 --> 00:47:17.396
♪ As the wind blows, ♪

00:47:17.729 --> 00:47:25.487
♪ along with the song,
I feel your hand. ♪

00:47:25.512 --> 00:47:30.183
♪ May my prayer be heard, ♪

00:47:30.534 --> 00:47:37.916
♪ that you love me in return. ♪

00:47:37.916 --> 00:47:42.546
♪ An orange sky, ♪

00:47:42.546 --> 00:47:49.469
♪ painting the beauty
of your eyes— ♪

00:47:49.469 --> 00:47:54.975
♪ My mind asks, ♪

00:47:55.000 --> 00:48:00.047
♪ do you also want to kiss me? ♪

00:48:01.603 --> 00:48:14.824
♪ Is this as far as
our friendship goes? ♪

00:48:16.684 --> 00:48:17.598
What’s it for?

00:48:17.623 --> 00:48:19.875
I got inspired by my friend.

00:48:19.875 --> 00:48:22.711
He wanted to
confess his feelings

00:48:22.711 --> 00:48:25.172
but couldn’t
because they’re friends.

00:48:25.172 --> 00:48:26.673
Just have a crush on me instead,

00:48:26.867 --> 00:48:28.661
since I have a crush
on you anyway.

00:48:29.635 --> 00:48:30.636
Via…

00:48:32.596 --> 00:48:34.389
I think I have feelings for you.

00:48:42.814 --> 00:48:44.066
How was it?

00:48:49.571 --> 00:48:50.572
Huh?

00:48:54.159 --> 00:48:55.160
It’s good.

00:48:56.244 --> 00:48:57.371
The song’s good.

00:48:57.704 --> 00:49:00.832
And your singing,
it’s really good too.

00:49:01.166 --> 00:49:06.838
It’s about someone
who wants to be honest

00:49:06.838 --> 00:49:08.048
about how they feel.

00:49:08.048 --> 00:49:10.300
Someone who wants to confess
to their friend, right?

00:49:10.884 --> 00:49:11.885
Why—

00:49:14.680 --> 00:49:17.557
Why did you write
a song like that?

00:49:20.435 --> 00:49:23.146
Via, are you okay?
Your face is red.

00:49:23.146 --> 00:49:24.731
- Huh?
- Are you okay?

00:49:25.023 --> 00:49:27.985
Me? No. I’m fine.
It’s just hot.

00:49:31.238 --> 00:49:34.157
It’s hot, and the
sun’s about to set.

00:49:34.157 --> 00:49:36.451
I still have to commute home.

00:49:36.451 --> 00:49:38.453
It might get too late, Kino.

00:49:38.453 --> 00:49:40.914
There’s traffic, it’ll get dark.
Come on, let’s go.

00:49:41.999 --> 00:49:43.083
Via, wait.

00:49:44.751 --> 00:49:45.794
So…

00:49:49.423 --> 00:49:50.716
How was the song?

00:49:54.011 --> 00:49:56.096
Did you understand it?

00:49:56.596 --> 00:49:57.431
Of course.

00:49:57.764 --> 00:49:59.307
And the song is good.

00:50:00.183 --> 00:50:01.518
It’s really good.

00:50:02.227 --> 00:50:05.564
It’s about admitting their
feelings to their friend, right?

00:50:05.564 --> 00:50:09.776
But they're scared it might
ruin the friendship.

00:50:11.570 --> 00:50:13.163
He confessed, right?

00:50:14.072 --> 00:50:16.074
What am I even
supposed to say?

00:50:16.363 --> 00:50:18.949
Can I really risk everything
we’ve been through?

00:50:19.428 --> 00:50:21.561
What if we break up?

00:50:21.586 --> 00:50:23.838
What’ll happen
to our friendship?

00:50:27.544 --> 00:50:28.545
And yeah.

00:50:29.296 --> 00:50:30.756
It’s a really good song.

00:50:31.048 --> 00:50:32.049
Let’s go.

00:50:32.074 --> 00:50:33.492
Via, I love you.

00:50:41.058 --> 00:50:42.642
Not just as a friend.

00:50:43.852 --> 00:50:45.437
I know you already know that,

00:50:45.812 --> 00:50:48.190
so why are you
still avoiding it?

00:50:51.276 --> 00:50:52.652
I already know what
you’re going to say.

00:50:52.652 --> 00:50:54.613
If you’re just going to
thank me, I don’t need it.

00:50:56.198 --> 00:50:58.194
What do you
even want me to say?

00:50:58.241 --> 00:50:59.910
What should I even say?

00:50:59.910 --> 00:51:01.620
Kino, I don’t know
what to do anymore.

00:51:01.620 --> 00:51:03.580
I don’t know what
to say because,

00:51:03.580 --> 00:51:05.665
why did you have
to say that before?

00:51:05.665 --> 00:51:07.709
Why do you still
have to say it now?

00:51:07.709 --> 00:51:08.710
Look at me, even now,

00:51:08.710 --> 00:51:10.545
I don’t know what
I’m supposed to feel.

00:51:10.545 --> 00:51:12.506
I don’t know what I really feel.

00:51:13.465 --> 00:51:15.008
Damn it, Larkin.

00:51:17.071 --> 00:51:18.489
How do you really feel?

00:51:19.054 --> 00:51:20.055
Do you love me?

00:51:20.055 --> 00:51:21.348
Of course!

00:51:27.020 --> 00:51:28.605
We’re friends, right?

00:51:36.988 --> 00:51:38.907
Come on, Via. Let’s go home.

00:51:48.324 --> 00:51:50.034
Come on.
I’ll bring you home.

00:51:50.317 --> 00:51:52.110
I also want to see
Papa and the kids.

00:52:00.846 --> 00:52:02.097
We’re here!

00:52:02.097 --> 00:52:02.973
Hi, Pa.

00:52:02.973 --> 00:52:04.057
- Hi, Via!
- Hey.

00:52:04.057 --> 00:52:04.933
Pa.

00:52:04.933 --> 00:52:05.725
- Arkin!
- Arkin!

00:52:05.725 --> 00:52:06.977
Hi!

00:52:07.269 --> 00:52:08.145
- Long time no see.
- Arkin!

00:52:08.145 --> 00:52:09.229
- Oh, Arkin!
- Papa.

00:52:09.229 --> 00:52:10.397
Glad you came to visit.

00:52:10.519 --> 00:52:12.396
Pa, I’ll sleep here
tonight, okay?

00:52:12.421 --> 00:52:14.818
But I’ll leave early tomorrow
since I have a shoot.

00:52:14.818 --> 00:52:17.445
Sure thing. You’re really
famous now, huh?

00:52:17.904 --> 00:52:20.657
Just don’t forget to
take care of yourself, okay?

00:52:20.657 --> 00:52:21.241
Yes, Pa.

00:52:21.241 --> 00:52:22.909
Oh, wait. Via, I cooked.

00:52:22.909 --> 00:52:24.077
You two eat first, okay?

00:52:24.077 --> 00:52:26.204
Sure, Pa. Let me
help you. I’ll do it.

00:52:26.204 --> 00:52:28.165
No, no. I’m fine. I got this.

00:52:29.065 --> 00:52:30.066
Okay.

00:52:31.099 --> 00:52:34.144
- So, how have you been?
- Wow, Arkin, it’s been a while, right?

00:52:34.546 --> 00:52:36.923
But we always see you on TV.

00:52:37.086 --> 00:52:38.338
How is it again?

00:52:39.801 --> 00:52:41.636
Refreshing!

00:52:42.429 --> 00:52:45.390
You know, Arkin, I think
I could be on TV too.

00:52:45.390 --> 00:52:46.210
Go ahead.

00:52:46.235 --> 00:52:47.945
Refreshing!

00:52:47.970 --> 00:52:50.303
It should be
a little gentler, like this.

00:52:51.646 --> 00:52:52.564
Refreshing.

00:52:52.564 --> 00:52:54.274
That’s how it
should be, you guys!

00:52:54.274 --> 00:52:57.652
Since you watch
my shows and my ads,

00:52:58.361 --> 00:52:59.779
I brought something
for you guys.

00:53:00.238 --> 00:53:01.364
Souvenirs!

00:53:01.364 --> 00:53:02.115
Wow!

00:53:02.115 --> 00:53:03.158
- Here’s yours.
- That’s a lot, Arkin.

00:53:03.158 --> 00:53:04.159
These are toys.

00:53:04.159 --> 00:53:05.410
Here are snacks.

00:53:05.410 --> 00:53:07.162
- This one too.
- Chocolates!

00:53:07.162 --> 00:53:08.914
Not now, okay? After dinner.

00:53:08.914 --> 00:53:10.707
This is my favorite!

00:53:10.707 --> 00:53:12.584
- Thank you, Arkin.
- Of course, I know. I know you well.

00:53:12.584 --> 00:53:13.627
- Here, this one’s for you.
- Look at this.

00:53:13.627 --> 00:53:14.711
- Thank you, Arkin!
- And this one, for you. Look.

00:53:14.920 --> 00:53:17.797
Can’t we just stay
like this? Happy.

00:53:17.797 --> 00:53:22.636
Uncomplicated.
Not ruining our friendship…

00:53:31.384 --> 00:53:32.385
Via?

00:53:41.696 --> 00:53:43.073
That’s my shirt.

00:53:46.927 --> 00:53:47.969
Oh my gosh.

00:53:47.994 --> 00:53:49.037
What do you want me to do?

00:53:49.037 --> 00:53:51.957
That was the first thing
I grabbed from the cabinet.

00:53:51.957 --> 00:53:54.042
Fine, fine, I’ll change—

00:53:54.042 --> 00:53:55.627
- I’ll return it to you.
- No, don’t. It’s fine.

00:54:15.730 --> 00:54:16.815
Move over.

00:54:24.030 --> 00:54:26.241
Via, we have a kissing
scene in our movie.

00:54:30.537 --> 00:54:31.538
So what?

00:54:32.038 --> 00:54:33.331
You’ve never had
your first kiss yet.

00:54:33.331 --> 00:54:35.333
Perfect timing, Clea’s there.
Don’t you want that?

00:54:37.303 --> 00:54:38.930
Via, I want it to be with you.

00:54:48.661 --> 00:54:49.913
Why me?

00:54:50.849 --> 00:54:52.017
I don’t want to.

00:54:52.461 --> 00:54:54.255
Not me. Just choose Clea.
I don’t know how.

00:54:59.524 --> 00:55:00.984
Why are you laughing?

00:55:00.984 --> 00:55:02.861
What’s funny? I’m serious.

00:55:02.861 --> 00:55:04.279
Clea’s right there.

00:55:05.155 --> 00:55:07.032
I’m sure she’s
better at it than I am.

00:55:07.032 --> 00:55:08.116
Just choose Clea.

00:55:08.116 --> 00:55:09.826
- Why?
- What?

00:55:09.826 --> 00:55:11.494
Is Clea the one I like?

00:55:17.032 --> 00:55:18.451
Admit it, Via.

00:55:18.835 --> 00:55:20.420
You’re falling for me.

00:55:24.758 --> 00:55:26.676
As if. Excuse me.

00:55:33.808 --> 00:55:35.018
You don’t want to admit it?

00:55:39.147 --> 00:55:41.316
Push me away if you’re
not in love with me.

00:56:44.671 --> 00:56:45.744
What about you?

00:56:46.047 --> 00:56:48.758
Don’t you like
anyone you work with?

00:56:49.206 --> 00:56:51.375
You’re surrounded by
so many pretty girls.

00:56:54.919 --> 00:56:56.796
Why are you asking that?

00:57:04.441 --> 00:57:05.817
Just kidding.

00:57:06.568 --> 00:57:07.610
No.

00:57:07.610 --> 00:57:09.279
I don’t like anyone there.

00:57:09.821 --> 00:57:11.573
You? Do you like anyone?

00:57:14.842 --> 00:57:17.721
You… You’re the one I like.

00:57:17.993 --> 00:57:21.914
But it can’t happen,
so being friends is fine.

00:57:25.619 --> 00:57:27.788
Because I like you.

00:57:40.185 --> 00:57:42.312
Whether we stay friends
or whatever we become,

00:57:42.312 --> 00:57:44.731
nothing’s going to
change between us, right?

00:57:44.731 --> 00:57:48.318
Here comes
the Box Office King!

00:57:48.318 --> 00:57:49.068
Oh my gosh, Via,

00:57:49.068 --> 00:57:50.695
they said there’s
a kissing scene.

00:57:51.488 --> 00:57:54.657
Here with us today is
the most handsome of them all,

00:57:54.657 --> 00:57:57.076
Mr. Larkin Sanchez.

00:57:57.076 --> 00:57:59.746
So, to answer
everyone’s question,

00:57:59.746 --> 00:58:02.790
is Larkin Sanchez still single?

00:58:04.078 --> 00:58:05.752
Oh, so you’re Rhythmics too?

